=== 批评 ===
儘管在新聞報導中受到極度的歡迎，OpenSocial在初期運行的並不好；它只在Google的[[Orkut|Orkut]]上運作，只有很少的工具，而且某些工具會傳回錯誤訊息。其他網路還在研究架構的使用。

根據TechCrunch在2007年11月5日的報導，OpenSocial也被破解了。據其報導，破解Ning上根基於OpenSocial的iLike的總共只花了20分鐘。攻擊者有辦法增加或移除使用者的播放表單上的歌曲，並查看他們的資料和朋友。<ref >{{cite web |url=http://techcrunch.com/2007/11/05/opensocial-hacked-again/ |title=OpenSocial Hacked Again |accessdate=2010-07-24 |last=Arrington |first=Michael |date=2007-11-05 |work=[[TechCrunch|TechCrunch]] |publisher= |doi= |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69Y7PNBoP?url=http://techcrunch.com/2007/11/05/opensocial-hacked-again/ |archivedate=2012-07-30 |quote= |dead-url=no }}</ref>

在12月6日，TechCrunch接著有了一篇MediaPops創建者拉斯·惠特曼（Russ Whitman）的報導，他聲稱「雖然我們一開始感到相當興奮，但我們已經知道艱辛的道路只是把本來就有限的釋出更加限制了」。他又補充說「核心功能元件」失蹤而且「寫一次，傳的遠」（"write once, distribute broadly"）並不精確。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://techcrunch.com/2007/12/06/opensocial-still-not-open-for-business/ |title=OpenSocial Still "Not Open for Business" |accessdate=2010-07-24 |last=Schonfeld |first=Erick |date=2007-12-06 |work=[[TechCrunch|TechCrunch]] |publisher= |doi= |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/69Y7QEl9n?url=http://techcrunch.com/2007/12/06/opensocial-still-not-open-for-business/ |archivedate=2012-07-30 |quote= |dead-url=no }}</ref>

===背景===
OpenSocial時常被描述為比[[Facebook|Facebook]]專有的[[社交網路服務|社交網路服務]][[Facebook_Platform|Facebook Platform]]更開放的[[跨平台|跨平台]]選擇。<ref name="NY Times">{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/10/31/technology/31google.html |title=Google and Friends to Gang Up on Facebook |accessdate=2007-10-31 |author= |last=Helft |first=Miguel |authorlink= |coauthors=Brad Stone |date=2007-10-31 |work=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]] |publisher=[[The_New_York_Times_Company|The New York Times Company]] |pages= |language= |doi= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090410071113/http://www.nytimes.com/2007/10/31/technology/31google.html |archivedate=2009-04-10 |quote= |dead-url=no }}</ref>在2007年5月Facebook Platform啟用以後，<ref name="Facebook Platform">{{cite web |url=http://www.facebook.com/press/releases.php?p=3102 |title=Facebook Unveils Platform for Developers of Social Applications |accessdate=2007-11-06 |date=2007-05-24 |publisher=[[Facebook|Facebook]] |doi= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071018164000/http://www.facebook.com/press/releases.php?p=3102 |archivedate=2007-10-18 |quote= |dead-url=no }}</ref>隨著2007年7月中併購新興的桌面工具網站公司[[Parakey|Parakey]]，<ref name="Parakey">{{cite web |url=http://ads.ak.facebook.com/ads/press/Parakey_Press_Release.pdf |title=Facebook Acquires Startup Parakey |accessdate=2007-11-06 |date=2007-07-19 |publisher=[[Facebook|Facebook]] |doi= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080307153749/http://ads.ak.facebook.com/ads/press/Parakey_Press_Release.pdf |archivedate=2008-03-07 |quote= |format=PDF |deadurl=yes }}</ref>快速成長的Facebook被廣泛報導為Google在建立和使用一個無所不在的網頁作業系統（{{lang|en|Web operating system}}）的挑戰對手。<ref name="butterfly">{{cite news |url=http://www.nytimes.com/2007/11/04/technology/04digi.html |title=Why Google Turned Into a Social Butterfly |accessdate=2007-11-06 |last=Stross |first=Randall |authorlink= |date=2007-11-04 |work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]: Digital Domain |publisher=[[The_New_York_Times_Company|The New York Times Company]] |doi= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090411083545/http://www.nytimes.com/2007/11/04/technology/04digi.html |archivedate=2009-04-11 |quote= |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Faceboook OS">{{cite web |url=http://www.redherring.com/Home/23046 |title=Is Facebook An Operating System? |accessdate=2007-11-06 |last=Dreyfuss |first=Joel |date=2007-10-26 |work= |publisher=Red Herring |doi= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071028070256/http://www.redherring.com/Home/23046 |archivedate=2007-10-28 |quote= |deadurl=yes }}</ref><ref name="Facebook next Microsoft">{{cite web |url=http://www.techcrunch.com/2007/07/19/could-facebook-become-the-next-microsoft/ |title=Could Facebook Become The Next Microsoft? |accessdate=2007-11-06 |last=Riley |first=Duncan |date=2007-07-19 |publisher=[[TechCrunch|TechCrunch]] |doi= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071031074121/http://www.techcrunch.com/2007/07/19/could-facebook-become-the-next-microsoft/ |archivedate=2007-10-31 |quote= |dead-url=no }}</ref>和在2007年9月網頁點閱量世界第二的Facebook比起來，Google的社交網路[[orkut|orkut]]在該月落居第六，而半數以上的使用者住在巴西。<ref name="butterfly" />

關於兩間公司之間競爭的報導隨著Facebook在Google原先排定要宣布他的社交網路的前一天<ref name="SocialAds TechCrunch">{{cite web |url=http://www.techcrunch.com/2007/10/30/facebooks-social-ad-network-what-we-think-we-know-so-far/ |title=Facebook’s Social Ad Network: What We (Think We) Know So Far |accessdate=2007-07-06 |last=Schonfeld |first=Erick |date=2007-10-30 |publisher=[[TechCrunch|TechCrunch]] |doi= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071031003743/http://www.techcrunch.com/2007/10/30/facebooks-social-ad-network-what-we-think-we-know-so-far/ |archivedate=2007-10-31 |quote= |dead-url=no }}</ref>（2007年11月6日<ref name="Facebook Ads">{{cite web |url=http://www.facebook.com/press/releases.php?p=9176 |title=Facebook Unveils Facebook Ads |accessdate=2007-11-06 |date=2007-11-06 |publisher=[[Facebook|Facebook]] |doi= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110601041418/https://www.facebook.com/press/releases.php?p=9176 |archivedate=2011-06-01 |quote= |dead-url=no }}</ref>）排定了一個[[網路廣告|網路廣告]]新計畫（叫做Facebook Ads）而升溫。這新計畫包含廣告服務和瞄準程式（分別叫做Facebook Social Ads and Facebook Insights）<ref name="Facebook Ads" />以對抗Google領導市場的[[Google_AdSense|AdSense]]和[[AdWords|AdWords]]程式。<ref name="GigaOm">{{cite web |url=http://gigaom.com/2007/11/06/facebook-vs-google/ |title=Why Is Google Afraid of Facebook? |accessdate=2007-11-06 |last=Malik |first=Om |authorlink=Om Malik |date=2007-11-06 |work=GigaOm |publisher=GigaOmniMedia |doi= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071107030836/http://gigaom.com/2007/11/06/facebook-vs-google/ |archivedate=2007-11-07 |quote= |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Mashable">{{cite web |url=http://mashable.com/2007/11/01/newsgator-opensocial/ |title=Newsgator Joins OpenSocial |accessdate=2008-01-24 |last=Nicole |first=Kristen |authorlink=Kristen Nicole |date=2007-11-01 |work=Mashable |publisher=Federated Media Publishing |doi= |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080212133228/http://mashable.com/2007/11/01/newsgator-opensocial/ |archivedate=2008-02-12 |quote= |dead-url=no }}</ref>

